                <p>Getting ready for a beach vacation or weekend camping trip? Hosting a backyard barbeque or graduation party? Canopy tents have become popular at these outdoor events because no other product offers a better combination of affordability, convenience, and protection from rain, wind, and sun.</p>
                <p>The <strong>best pop up canopy tents</strong> are designed to keep you dry with waterproof polyester canopies, stop strong winds with sidewall attachments, and block UV rays with high UPF materials. But there is also a growing number of brands selling cheap alloy steel frames that are prone to toppling and made with canopy fabric so thin it will leave you soaked or sunburnt.</p>
                <h3>What should you consider when choosing a canopy tent?</h3>
                <p>The answer isn&apos;t the same for everyone and it largely depends on the intended use. If you are traveling to the beach, you&apos;ll want a lightweight and portable canopy with a rust-resistant frame. If you are hosting an outdoor event, a large pop up tent with a durable steel frame big enough to accommodate a table and chairs. Going on a camping trip? A camping canopy that is water resistant and has mosquito nets or mesh screen sidewalls to help keep you dry and insect free.</p>
                <p>In this article, we highlight the best canopy tent for each of these outdoor use cases and explain in detail why we arrived at that decision. Over the past 6 years, we have become the most trusted source for canopy tent reviews having spent over 3,000 hours researching, reviewing, and testing dozens of instant pop up canopy tents in the sun, wind, and rain. Ultimately we hope this information helps you find the shelter that perfectly suits your needs.</p>
